In this article, President Trump welcomes members of the Congressional Black Caucus to the White House. He expresses his commitment to improving conditions for African American citizens, stating that every American child has the right to grow up in a safe community, attend great schools, and have access to high-paying jobs. He criticizes the amount of money spent overseas while neglecting the needs of American children in cities like Baltimore, Chicago, and Detroit. Trump acknowledges the contributions of African American citizens to the country and discusses his plans to lower drug prices through a strong bidding process. He emphasizes the importance of addressing this issue, stating that people are being ripped off when they need prescription drugs. Trump concludes by expressing his appreciation for the members of the Congressional Black Caucus being present and his desire to work together to accomplish various goals.